{
  "text": "One group used 3-dimensional (3D) MRI to measure the total cartilaginous volume and the volume of the ossific nuclei in both the talus and calcaneum. [CITATION_1] They found that these measurements were less in clubfoot than in normal feet. In particular, the volume of the nucleus of the talus was found to be 20% smaller in affected feet. They also found that the ossific nucleus in both the talus and calcaneum of patients with clubfoot lies more anterior than in the normal foot.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "6175504"
